        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10572",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sparky",
                        "name": "sparky",
                        "displayName": "Mark Evans",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I'm not sure I understand this report. Can you provide a short code sample which demonstrates this?\n\nLooking at the above code sample you are calling fetchAll statically but its not a static method.\n\nSee http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/manual\/en\/zend.db.table.html#zend.db.table.fetchmultiple",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sparky",
                        "name": "sparky",
                        "displayName": "Mark Evans",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-21T06:20:14.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-21T06:20:14.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10573",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=superbiji",
                        "name": "superbiji",
                        "displayName": "Superbiji",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "updated",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=superbiji",
                        "name": "superbiji",
                        "displayName": "Superbiji",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-21T06:26:34.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-21T06:26:34.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10577",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sparky",
                        "name": "sparky",
                        "displayName": "Mark Evans",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I still dont understand your problem :(\n\nYour still calling Zend_DB_Table::fetchAll statically when its not a static method.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=sparky",
                        "name": "sparky",
                        "displayName": "Mark Evans",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-07-21T16:57:42.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-07-21T16:57:42.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10684",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Perhaps posting a simple example showing how to fetch and echo all rows in a table would help.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=gavin",
                        "name": "gavin",
                        "displayName": "Gavin",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-08-07T17:32:51.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-08-07T17:32:51.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10861",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=toomuchphp",
                        "name": "toomuchphp",
                        "displayName": "Peter Hodge",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem is in Zend_Db_Table::_fetch(), this line in particular:\n\n        \/\/ the WHERE clause\n        $where = (array) $where;\n\nWhen Superbiji uses empty string, $where becomes an array containing an empty string and Zend_Db_Table tries to make \"WHERE [empty string] ORDER BY ...\".  If he was to use NULL, $where becomes an empty array and works correctly.  He should be able to use empty string (or zero, or false, for that matter).  Recommend changing the line to:\n\n        \/\/ the WHERE clause\n        if(is_null($where))\n            $where = array();\n        elseif(!is_array($where))\n            $where = array($where);\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=toomuchphp",
                        "name": "toomuchphp",
                        "displayName": "Peter Hodge",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-20T23:27:15.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-20T23:27:15.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/10904",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=toomuchphp",
                        "name": "toomuchphp",
                        "displayName": "Peter Hodge",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Oops, I was obviously off with the fairies when I posted that fix (as it doesn't fix anything).  Recommend changing to *this* instead:\n\n{noformat}\n  \/\/ the WHERE clause\n  if(empty($where))\n    $where = array();\n  elseif(!is_array($where))\n    $where = array($where);\n{noformat}\n",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=toomuchphp",
                        "name": "toomuchphp",
                        "displayName": "Peter Hodge",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2006-09-26T19:32:49.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2006-09-26T19:32:49.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/11456",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/framework.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=bkarwin",
